Date: Wed, 4 Sep 2024 09:12:55 +0200
Subject: ACPI: battery: use DEFINE_SIMPLE_DEV_PM_OPS
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Patch-mainline: v6.13-rc1
Git-commit: a56fdd874301c3a2d27097a7084467ab5bdc6815
References: jsc#PED-12273

Use the recommended macro to define the PM ops.

Also use pm_sleep_ptr() when assigning the ops to the driver.
This allows the removal of the ifdef CONFIG_PM_SLEEP.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Wei√üschuh <linux@weissschuh.net>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20240904-acpi-battery-cleanups-v1-4-a3bf74f22d40@weissschuh.net
Signed-off-by: Rafael J. Wysocki <rafael.j.wysocki@intel.com>
Acked-by: Chun-Yi Lee <jlee@suse.com>
---
 drivers/acpi/battery.c |    8 ++------
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/acpi/battery.c
+++ b/drivers/acpi/battery.c
@@ -1277,7 +1277,6 @@ static void acpi_battery_remove(struct a
 	sysfs_remove_battery(battery);
 }
 
-#ifdef CONFIG_PM_SLEEP
 /* this is needed to learn about changes made in suspended state */
 static int acpi_battery_resume(struct device *dev)
 {
@@ -1294,11 +1293,8 @@ static int acpi_battery_resume(struct de
 	acpi_battery_update(battery, true);
 	return 0;
 }
-#else
-#define acpi_battery_resume NULL
-#endif
 
-static SIMPLE_DEV_PM_OPS(acpi_battery_pm, NULL, acpi_battery_resume);
+static DEFINE_SIMPLE_DEV_PM_OPS(acpi_battery_pm, NULL, acpi_battery_resume);
 
 static struct acpi_driver acpi_battery_driver = {
 	.name = "battery",
@@ -1308,7 +1304,7 @@ static struct acpi_driver acpi_battery_d
 		.add = acpi_battery_add,
 		.remove = acpi_battery_remove,
 		},
-	.drv.pm = &acpi_battery_pm,
+	.drv.pm = pm_sleep_ptr(&acpi_battery_pm),
 	.drv.probe_type = PROBE_PREFER_ASYNCHRONOUS,
 };
 
